title: Ella Fitzgerald - Live at Mister Kelly's 1958 (Verve, 2007) @
description:
Released to coincide with the 90th anniversary of Fitzgerald&#039;s birth, this is one of several live  albums that Fitzgerald recorded in the late 1950&#039;s. Sarah Vaughan had recorded an album at Mister Kelly&#039;s several months earlier.

This was a rare outing for several of the songs on this album. Fitzgerald had only recorded "Your Red Wagon" as a single, and this was the only time that Fitzgerald had sung "Across the Alley from the Alamo", as well as her only recording of "In the Wee Small Hours of the Morning" and her debut recording of "Witchcraft".

Highly recommended!

Personnel:
Ella Fitzgerald - vocals
Lou Levy - piano
Max Bennett - double bass
Gus Johnson - drums

Recorded August 10, 1958 at Mister Kelly&#039;s, Chicago:
